1. Project Abstract
This project, an Ultrasonic Radar System (or Sweeping Sonar), is designed to detect and map the location of objects within a specific radial area. The system utilizes the Time-of-Flight (ToF) sensing method, a core principle of acoustics, by employing an HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensor to measure the distance to an object. This sensor is mounted on a Servo Motor which rotates, allowing the system to sweep a 180-degree field of view. An Arduino Uno acts as the central control unit, managing the angular movement, performing high-speed ToF calculations, and transmitting the resulting ( Distance) data serially to a connected computer. The expected outcome is the real-time visualization of the surrounding environment displayed on computer.
